            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't think this addresses the root cause of the crash.\n\nWhat I think is happening is the `DiagnosticChanged` autocommand calling `nvim__redraw` is invoked via `on_detach` at a bad time; there's an issue where `close_buffer` triggers `on_detach` after `buf_freeall` while there's still a window temporarily open to the closed buffer.\n\nRebasing #34024 seems to fix the crash without the need for extra checks; I need to get around to finishing it, though.\n(To be clear, I'm not against checking `nvim_buf_is_loaded` for now as a workaround)",
